                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="Job-009-fn1" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: The Karaim equivalent
                            of the standard Hebrew Job 9:1 is not included in the text, probably
                            intentionally, see Job 3:1, 4:1, etc. for similar cases. The text is
                            reconstructed here on the basis of ADub.III.84. The Hebrew text is not
                            omitted, see BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;"
                                >וַיַּעַן אִיֹּוב וַיֹּאמַר </foreign>
                            ‘Then Job answered and said’ (Job 9:1). | C: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Ijov
                                da ajtty</emph>. | QB: <emph>Da ǯoɣap berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>Da qaruv berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>. | Kobeckaitė
                            (2019): <emph>Da qaruv berdi Ijov da ajtty</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-009-fn2" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: <emph>temanyn</emph>;
                            a scribal error.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-009-fn3" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>tergevsiz</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-009-fn4" type="footnote">JSul.I.04:
                            <emph>jengillek</emph>; probably a scribal error. Theoretically
                            speaking, an <emph>rl</emph> &amp;gt; <emph>ll</emph> assimilation could
