                            | C: <emph>jeŋil</emph>. | QB:<emph> jeŋil</emph>. | ADub.III.82:
                                <emph>jengilrek</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                            <emph>jengilŕak</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-009-fn5" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>gerebleri</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-009-fn6" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>görebleri byla evenin</emph>, introduced by the Hebrew phrasae
                                <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמר </foreign>
                            ‘or you will say’, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">עִם־אֳנִיּוֹת אֵבֶה </foreign>
