                                <emph>gemilär bilän kiläkniŋ</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>gerebler
                                byla klevčiler tez barma</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>gerabĺari byla Evenin</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-009-fn7" type="footnote">JSul.I.04:
                            <emph>kemesejim</emph>; a scribal error.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-009-fn8" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>kiplenejim</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-009-fn9" type="footnote">An alternative translation to
                                <emph>qolun</emph>, introduced with Heb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או </foreign>
                            ‘or’, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">יָדוֹ </foreign>
                            ‘his hand’. | C: <emph>qolun</emph>. | QB: <emph>qolun</emph>. |
                            ADub.III.84: <emph>qolun</emph>. | Kobeckaitė (2019):
                                <emph>keńašin</emph>.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
